<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-03-09T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-03-09T18:00:00-05:00" n="352" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d352">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">860S.5151/3–548: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the United States Political Adviser</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Joyce</hi></persName>), <hi rend="italic">at
                                Trieste</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                                <lb/>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">urgent</hi>
                            </seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-03-09T18:00:00-05:00">March 9,
                                    1948—6 p. m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>96. <gloss target="#t_urtel1">Urtel</gloss> 108 March 5.<note n="1" xml:id="d352fn1">In this telegram, not printed, Joyce referred to a
                                report that Secretary Marshall requested Congress for $20 million
                                for Trieste through the fiscal year 1949. He asked about the
                                specific purpose of this sum: to combat disease and unrest, or to
                                foster economic rehabilitation. (860S.5151/3–548)</note> Confirm
                                <gloss target="#t_Deptel1">Deptel</gloss> same date 91.<note n="2" xml:id="d352fn2">Not printed.</note> Proposed $20 million program
                            covers chiefly items now supplied <gloss target="#t_PL1">PL</gloss> 84.
                            Tentative breakdown 15–month program follows (all figures in long
                            tons):</p>
                        <p>Wheat 62.180, edible fats (lard) 3.820, horsemeat 810, milk, evaporated
                            5,090, pulses 5,100, coal 240,000 and industrial fats 900. Also $315
                            thousand for medical supplies and $200 thousand for fibers incentive and
                            other goods.</p>
                        <p>Sent to Rome.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Marshall</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>